Question Text: Unlike our five-layer model, the OSI network model adds two more layers on top of the Application Layer. Select examples of these new layers below.
Choices:
a. The compression layer
b. The session layer
c. The interconnection layer
d. The presentation layer
LLM Explanation: The OSI network model adds two more layers on top of the Application Layer: the Presentation Layer and the Session Layer. Among the given choices, the Session Layer (option b) is one of the additional layers in the OSI model. The Presentation Layer (option d) is the other additional layer. The Compression Layer (option a) and the Interconnection Layer (option c) are not part of the additional layers introduced by the OSI model.

Question Text: Which of the following sections of the TCP/IP Five-Layer Network Model contain the data the application wants to send? Select all that apply.
Choices:
a. The payload section of the Ethernet frame
b. The payload section of the IP Datagram
c. The payload of the TCP segment
d. The header of the Ethernet frame
LLM Explanation: The data that the application wants to send is contained in the payload of the TCP segment. The TCP segment encapsulates the application data before it is further encapsulated into an IP datagram and then into an Ethernet frame. The payload section of the TCP segment carries the actual data from the application layer.
